Context: This course is a Degree Preparation program offered at George Brown College's St. James "A" building located at 200 King Street East. The specific duration and start dates are yet to be determined. Students will study topics including biochemistry, nutritional science, medical technologies, biotechnology, pathogens and disease, and public health issues. The college has an articulation agreement with 14 participating colleges that allows EAP graduates to satisfy English language proficiency requirements without further testing for a diploma program. For more information about the U-Level Bridging program, students can email gbcdegreebridging@georgebrown.ca or call (416) 415-5000 ext. 3683. The college's website contains subject to change and should not be considered a representation, offer, or warranty. For application deadlines, college news, upcoming events, tours, and more, students can sign up on the website. Additional contact information includes phone number 416-415-2000, TTY: 1-877-515-5559, email ask.george@georgebrown.ca, and social media hub.
